From a4dac0e2dbeb2b818465c0d80412d210a64ee280 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: TBFS Security Review <review@tbfs.local>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 09:37:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 10/10] F-11/F-19/F-17: test suite + CI; correct the 9%/12% doc
 contradiction
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- tests/calculations.test.mjs, tests/app-state.test.mjs (node:test, no
  deps): lock the reference standard loan (R10,000/10mo → R11,100
  interest, R22,900 total, R2,290/mo), the payment waterfall order and
  interest-cap clamp, the 7-day penalty cap, the schedule start-year and
  due-date roll, the timezone-safe membership date, tier self-
  consistency, and the importJSON accept/reject contract. 22 tests. (F-11/F-19)
- .github/workflows/tests.yml: node --test + the inline-script syntax
  gate on every push/PR.
- TBFS-COMPLETE-BUSINESS-RULES.md: the standard-loan initiation fee said
  '9% / × 0.09' in three places but the worked example and the code bill
  12% (R1,200 on R10,000) — corrected to 12%, with a canonical-rates
  banner pointing at Calculations.RATES + the test suite as the single
  source of truth. STOCKVEL-30K-6M-CALCULATION.md: added a note that its
  hand-worked figures are internally inconsistent and the code is
  authoritative.
- shared/navigation.js and shared/sw-register.js: lifecycle logs gated
  behind DEBUG, completing the F-17 sweep across shared/.
